etomica.threaded.domain

Class MEAMMd3DThreaded

  • java.lang.Object
    • etomica.simulation.Simulation
      • etomica.threaded.domain.MEAMMd3DThreaded
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISimulation

    public class MEAMMd3DThreaded
extends Simulation
    Molecular-Dynamics Simulation Using the Modified Embedded-Atom Method (MEAM) Potential. The MEAM potential is intended for use with metallic and covalently-bonded solid systems. The MEAM potential for an atom is built using terms describing parts of the relationships between the atom and each of its neighbors, the number of which is determined by a cutoff and/or screening function. Each type of pair- wise term is summed over all the neighbors, and then used in expressions describing the embedding energy and the repulsive energy of the atom. Effectively, the MEAM potential is a many-body potential. This class was adapted from LjMd3D.java by K.R. Schadel and A. Schultz in July 2005. Initially, it employed a version of the embedded-atom method potential, and was later adapted in February 2006 to use the modified embedded-atom method potential.
